Lagos – Chairman of Innoson Motors, Mr. Innocent Chukuwuma, has been declared wanted by Justice Mojisola Dada of a Special Offences Court, Ikeja, Lagos, following his refusal to attend court proceedings for his fraud trial. Chukwuma was arraigned along with his company for alledgedly forging documents to facilitate the clearing of some goods at the port. He was alledged to have forged documents purportedly emanating from GTB Bank. This issue has generated uproar with Innoson alledging victimization and harassment by Economic and Financial Crimes and GTB Bank. He arraignment before the court has however failed due to his consistently failure to appear in court. His lawyers also have a running battle with the presiding judge during the proceedings in court. Details later… 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 